io.github.nixtabyte.telegram.jtelebot.server.impl

Class AbstractCommandDispatcher

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.github.nixtabyte.telegram.jtelebot.server.impl.AbstractCommandDispatcher
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CommandDispatcher, Service, Runnable, Observer
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DefaultCommandDispatcher

    public abstract class AbstractCommandDispatcher
extends Object
implements CommandDispatcher, Observer, Service, Runnable
    Abstract implementation of CommandDispatcher, Observer, Service and Runnable which uses a runnable thread with a service pattern behavior (start|stop) in order to enqueue Command objects and then execute them one by one.

    It also implements an Observer pattern behavior in order to be able to "observe" or be aware when an observable object changes its current state. In a common Observer scenario, the observable object would send a notification to every Observer class hooked and this way the Observer would be able to perform a particular action after the signal.
    Since:
    0.0.1
    See Also:
    Command, CommandDispatcher, Observer, Service, Runnable
